---
import BaseLayout from '../../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Apostille Services Dubai - Hague Convention Document Authentication | OnlineTranslation.ae"
  description="Apostille services for Hague Convention countries. Simplified document authentication for UAE use. Guidance on apostille vs embassy legalization requirements."
>
  <section class="hero-section bg-dark" data-theme="dark">
    <div class="container">
      <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">HOME</a>
        <span class="separator">&gt;</span>
        <a href="/services/attestation/">ATTESTATION</a>
        <span class="separator">&gt;</span>
        <span class="current">APOSTILLE</span>
      </nav>

      <h1>Apostille Services</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">Hague Convention Authentication</p>
      <p class="hero-intro">For documents from Hague Convention member countries, an apostille provides simplified authentication that is recognized internationally. While UAE is not a Hague member, apostilled documents still require embassy attestation for full UAE acceptance. We guide you through the complete process.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Understanding Apostille Authentication</h2>

      <div class="info-grid">
        <div class="info-card">
          <i class="fas fa-certificate"></i>
          <h3>What is an Apostille?</h3>
          <p>An apostille is a standardized certificate that authenticates documents for use in countries that are members of the Hague Apostille Convention.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-card highlight">
          <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i>
          <h3>UAE Requirement</h3>
          <p>Since UAE is not a Hague member, apostilled documents still require UAE Embassy attestation followed by MOFA attestation for official use.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-card">
          <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
          <h3>Simplified First Step</h3>
          <p>Apostille replaces the need for home country ministry authentication, making it a faster first step in the attestation chain.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-light">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Apostille Process for UAE Documents</h2>

      <div class="process-flow">
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="step-number">1</div>
          <h3>Apostille</h3>
          <p>Obtain apostille from competent authority in issuing country (replaces ministry authentication)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-arrow"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i></div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="step-number">2</div>
          <h3>UAE Embassy</h3>
          <p>Submit apostilled document to UAE Embassy for attestation stamp</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-arrow"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i></div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="step-number">3</div>
          <h3>MOFA</h3>
          <p>Final attestation by UAE Ministry of Foreign Affairs</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Common Apostille Countries</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">Major Hague Convention member countries for UAE expat documents.</p>

